<br>
I had some troubles soloing there at 51, but I had crappy gear too.  With the weapons 51's have these days and a Fungi, it should be cake.<br>
<br>
The biggest problem with soloing the Hole entrance is runners.  There are two solutions I came up with.<br>
<br>
1) Pop in your FBE and fight them in the water.  Pull them to the furthest back corner underwater (just past the zone tunnel).  They take a long underwater path from there, so you usually have more than enough time to kill them.<br>
<br>
2) If you have good haste (i.e. CoF/RBB + Eyepatch) and fast weapons, just try to make them stutter path.  When a fleeing mob is hit, it often changes direction along the path.  If you hit them fast enough, they will just keep turning back and forth.  Just make sure when you first pull them, you pull them all the way back on the little walkway along the water.<br>
<br>
I suppose you could make a case for 3) Use a snare whip.  I never had one, but I would imagine that for a lvl 51, unless you have absurdly high natural dex, it would be unreliable. <p><table cellpadding="1" border="0" cellspacing="0">
